    distinct bugs:
    
    1. c_mock_idp::ac_on_message read the request URL from key
       "request_url", but ghttp_parser publishes it under "url"
       (kernel/c/root-linux/src/ghttp_parser.c:236). Result: every URL
       fell through to the 404 branch, including the discovery GET, and
       result_save_discovery rejected the response with status=404.
    
    2. c_test_driver::ac_on_token called gobj_stop_tree(priv->gobj_task)
       synchronously from inside EV_ON_TOKEN. That event is published by
       result_get_token while C_TASK::ac_on_message is still iterating
       priv->jobs. The stop ran C_TASK_AUTHENTICATE::mt_stop
       (EXEC_AND_RESET cleared priv->gobj_http to NULL) and C_TASK::mt_stop
       (priv->idx_job reset to 0); when ac_on_message resumed it did
       idx_job++ (0->1) and re-ran action_get_token with a NULL http
       client -> "hgobj dst NULL" + "Destroying a RUNNING gobj". Replace
       the synchronous stop with just dying=TRUE + 200ms death timer; the
       chain (logout) drains naturally and yuno teardown runs in order.
    
    3. set_expected_results was called from run_task_authenticate_test
       BEFORE yuneta_entry_point. yuneta_entry_point installs the gbmem
       allocators in jansson via json_set_alloc_funcs (entry_point.c:418).
       So the json_array() / json_pack-built expected_log_messages were
       libc-allocated; later test_json(NULL) in cleaning() decref'd them
       through gbmem_free -> "dl_delete: Deleting item with DIFFERENT
       dl_list_t" + "free(): invalid pointer" at exit. Fix: change the
       API to take const char *expected_log_msg, store it in a static,
       and build the json_t inside register_yuno_and_more (which runs
       after yuneta_entry_point has wired up the allocators). The four
       main_test*.c are updated to pass a string instead of a pre-packed
       json_t *.
    
