    Why
    ---
    The previous implementation propagated a `translate` attr through
    shellŌåÆnavs and rebuilt the nav DOMs on every language switch via
    yui_nav_rebuild + rebuild_toolbar. That was both heavier than needed
    and incompatible with components that already use the canonical
    data-i18n / refresh_language flow. It also failed silently in the
    test app (UI stayed in English on click), which is what triggered
    the rewrite.
    
    The right pattern, used everywhere else in the repo, is:
    
      1. Render every translatable text node with `data-i18n="key"`.
      2. To switch language, call `refresh_language(element, t)`. It
         walks every [data-i18n] descendant and replaces the first text
         node with `t(key)`. No DOM rebuild.
    
