        the cursor onto the last content row's last cell, which was
        still off the name column.
      - Adding the col-0 double-write parked the cursor at (last_row, 1)
        ŌĆö precisely the "second character in reverse on the last row"
        the user reported from the screenshot.
    
    leaveok(popup_wn, TRUE) tells ncurses "don't use this window's
    cursor to decide where the hardware cursor goes". With that set,
    the subsequent wnoutrefresh(l->wn) (editline) owns the cursor
    position, which is what we wanted all along ŌĆö the block cursor
    sits on the edit line at the end of the previewed candidate.
    
