    fix(c_editline): use mvwchgat for popup selection highlight
    
    The completion popup had a cosmetic bug: on ncurses clients (ycli,
    mqtt_tui) the cell at column 0 of a row that had just lost its
    A_REVERSE selection kept the inverse background. The per-cell
    chtype path, even with wclear + wbkgd + touchwin + explicit
    wattrset(A_NORMAL), didn't reliably invalidate that cell ŌĆö an
    ncurses diff optimisation (still not fully pinned down, see
    yunos/c/yuno_cli/TODO.md) was skipping the attr-only change when
    the character underneath (a leading space) matched the previous
    render.
    
    Switch to the two-pass render the ncurses menu/form libraries use:
    
      Pass 1 (content)
        wattrset(A_NORMAL) + werase, then waddnstr of the row text at
        (row, 0). The rest of the row is padded with waddch(' ') so
        every cell carries a real char that the attr pass can repaint.
    
      Pass 2 (attributes)
        mvwchgat(row, 0, w, A_NORMAL, def_pair, NULL) on every content
        row, then mvwchgat(row, 0, w, A_REVERSE, def_pair, NULL) on the
        selected one. mvwchgat is the public ncurses entry point for
        "change the attributes of a range of cells" ŌĆö unlike the char
        path it doesn't rely on chtype equality for diffing, so every
        cell is marked dirty and the physical terminal is told to repaint
        exactly which attrs each column carries.
    
    The status row path is untouched (still wattron(A_DIM) + mvwaddnstr
    on row 0 after werase ŌĆö it doesn't share the highlight and isn't
    affected by the bug).
    
