    test10_kc_silence ran end-to-end:
    
    1) status_str(504) had no case 504, so it fell through to the default
       "500 Internal Server Error".  ac_kc_watchdog called
       send_error_response(504, status_str(504), ...), which then emitted
       HTTP/1.1 500 Internal Server Error on the wire even though the
       numeric status field said 504.  Browsers/clients parsing the status
       line saw 500 and the test driver failed.  Added 504 (and 503 for
       completeness with line 1810's literal "503 Service Unavailable").
    
    2) ac_kc_watchdog did gobj_send_event(gobj, EV_END_TASK, 0, gobj),
       routing EV_END_TASK to ITSELF.  That fired ac_end_task and ran the
       local cleanup (priv->gobj_http, watchdog flag, browser_src), but
       the actual C_TASK child was still in the middle of waiting for
       Keycloak ŌĆö nobody stopped it.  It lingered RUNNING until yuno
       teardown, where the destroy walk hit "Destroying a RUNNING gobj"
       and the cancel CQEs of its internal C_TIMER tripped "Destroying a
       running event".
    
       Fix: track the in-flight task in priv->gobj_task (set in
       process_next, cleared in ac_end_task and mt_stop).  ac_end_task
       has two callers:
