    =========
    mt_create:     creates kc_watchdog as a C_TIMER0 pure child.
    mt_start:      gobj_start(kc_watchdog) so set_timeout0 works later.
    mt_stop:       clear_timeout0 + gobj_stop.  Also already tears down
                   priv->gobj_http and the inbound bottom from a
                   previous commit.
    process_next:  after starting the task, stashes active_browser_src
                   and, if kc_timeout_ms > 0, arms the watchdog.
    ac_kc_watchdog (NEW, bound to EV_TIMEOUT):
                   - st_kc_timeouts++
                   - gobj_log_error so the timeout is visible without
                     enabling traces
                   - if browser still alive, send_error_response 504
