    The previous draft added a raw PUBLIC c_auth_bff_get_status() to the
    header so the yuno could query each per-channel BFF's state. That
    violates the GClass interface convention: a gclass .h should expose
    only register_c_xxx and GOBJ_DECLARE_GCLASS, and everything else must
    go through attributes, commands, events, local methods or statistics.
    
    Replace the raw accessor with two idiomatic channels:
    
    1. view-status command (rich snapshot, including the queue contents)
    
       - C_AUTH_BFF now declares a command_table with help + view-status.
       - cmd_view_status returns {processing, has_active_http, active_http,
         q_count/head/tail/max, queue: [{action, browser_src}, ...]} via
         msg_iev_build_response.
       - C_AUTH_BFF_YUNO's view-bff-status command walks __bff_side__ for
         C_AUTH_BFF children with gobj_match_children_tree, calls each
         child's view-status via gobj_command(child, "view-status", ...),
         unwraps the {data} envelope with KW_EXTRACT, and aggregates totals
         (instances, processing, with_active_http, queued, max_q_count).
    
    2. SDF_RSTATS counters (collected automatically by gobj_stats)
    
       Eight resettable stats in attrs_table:
         - requests_total : browser requests accepted (any endpoint)
         - q_count        : current pending queue depth
         - q_max_seen     : high-water mark of queue depth
         - q_full_drops   : requests rejected because queue was full
         - kc_calls       : Keycloak round-trips started
         - kc_ok          : Keycloak round-trips returning 200
         - kc_errors      : Keycloak round-trips returning non-200
         - bff_errors    : 4xx/5xx returned to the browser
    
       Updated at the right code points: enqueue (count, max_seen,
       requests_total, drops on full), dequeue (count), process_next
       (kc_calls), result_token_response and result_kc_logout (kc_ok or
       kc_errors based on status), send_error_response (bff_errors,
       covering all 12 callsites). A small incr_stat() helper does the
       read+1+write dance over the typed attribute.
    
    GOBJ_DECLARE_GCLASS(C_AUTH_BFF) is now also declared in the header so
    external modules can reference the gclass name in filters like
    gobj_match_children_tree({"__gclass_name__": C_AUTH_BFF}).
    
    Net effect: priv->q_count and priv->processing stay as hot fields for
    the trace and the command snapshot, the typed counters mirror them so
    the agent can chart and reset them, and the rich queue view is
    reachable via gobj_command on each instance or in aggregate via the
    yuno-level view-bff-status.
    
