    fix: mbedTLS server no longer requires client certificates
    
    When ssl_trusted_certificate was configured, mbedTLS set authmode to
    VERIFY_REQUIRED for both client and server roles. This forced the server
    to demand a client certificate, breaking connections from clients that
    don't present one (which worked fine with OpenSSL).
    
    Now the server uses VERIFY_OPTIONAL (validate if presented, don't require)
    while clients keep VERIFY_REQUIRED to always verify the server certificate.
    
