    Fix mbedTLS bad_record_mac: accumulate TLS records in output_buffer before writing
    
    mbedtls_ssl_write() calls send_callback once per TLS record (~16 KB).
    For large payloads (e.g. 138 MB) this produced ~8000+ separate io_uring
    writes to the same fd, which could be reordered on the wire, corrupting
    TLS record order and causing bad_record_mac on the peer (browser).
    
    The fix adds an output_buffer to sskt_t. send_callback now appends to
