    New yuno that deploys the kernel C_AUTH_BFF GClass as a standalone
    HTTPS service. Mediates OAuth2 flows between browser SPAs and Keycloak,
    storing tokens as httpOnly cookies (SEC-06).
    
    The GClass implementation lives in the kernel (c_auth_bff.c/h).
    This yuno is a minimal wrapper with:
    - main.c: entry point, config, and GClass registration
    - CMakeLists.txt: standard yuno build (no external dependencies)
    - docs/README.txt: architecture and deployment notes
    
    One instance per realm, managed by yuneta_agent. Listens on HTTPS
    (default port 1801) alongside the WebSocket yuno (port 1800).
    Cookies are scoped to the hostname (no port) so they are sent
    automatically with WebSocket HTTP Upgrade requests.
    
