    mbedtls/helpers: fix WANT stall loop and CRLF parsing
    
    Two further issues found during security review of CONFIG_HAVE_MBEDTLS
    and CONFIG_FULLY_STATIC additions:
    
    1. mbedtls.c encrypt_data(): unbounded WANT_READ/WANT_WRITE retry loop
    
       When mbedtls_ssl_write() returns WANT_READ (TLS state machine needs
       incoming network data, e.g. a post-handshake KeyUpdate) the loop calls
       flush_clear_data() and retries immediately.  If the network has not
       yet delivered the required bytes, flush_clear_data() returns nothing
       and the loop spins forever, hanging the process.
    
       Fix: count consecutive WANT_* returns; after 5 fruitless attempts log
       a warning and return -1.  The counter resets to 0 after each successful
       mbedtls_ssl_write() so only a true stall triggers the limit.
    
    2. helpers.c parse_passwd_line / parse_group_line: \r not stripped
    
       Both parsers strip the trailing '\n' from the last field but not '\r'.
       If /etc/passwd or /etc/group was written with CRLF line endings (e.g.
       copied from a Windows host or an editor that adds CR), the last field
       retains the '\r'.  This silently breaks strcmp() calls such as
       strcmp(gr->gr_name, "yuneta") in is_yuneta_user(), causing the static
       build to always deny group membership.
    
       Fix: after stripping '\n', also strip '\r' from the last field in
       both parse_passwd_line (shell field) and parse_group_line (members
       field).
    
