    json_t and gbuffer_t patterns. This generically prevents any consumer
    from destroying a shared topic while others are still using it.
    
    tranger2 changes:
    - tranger2_open_topic: set __refcount__=1 for new topics, increment for
      existing (already-opened) topics
    - tranger2_close_topic: decrement refcount, only actually close (FDs,
      watchers, remove from dict) when refcount reaches 0
    - tranger2_delete_topic: decrement refcount, only delete from disk when
      refcount reaches 0
    - tranger2_stop: force refcount=1 before closing (shutdown override)
    - tranger2_backup_topic: force refcount=1 before closing (needs
      exclusive access)
    
    MQTT broker changes:
    - close_queues: remove session_taken_over hack, rely on topic refcount.
      For persistent sessions, call tranger2_close_topic to properly
      decrement the refcount (previously topics were left open indefinitely)
