    Implement the 5 commented-out functions that were blocking QoS 1 and
    QoS 2 message delivery through the broker:
    
    - message__release_to_inflight(): iterate inflight queue, find messages
      in mosq_ms_invalid state, assign mid, update state to wait_for_puback
      (QoS 1) or wait_for_pubrec (QoS 2), and send PUBLISH
    
    - message__out_update(): find message by mid in outgoing queue, verify
      QoS matches, update state via user_flag (used by client on PUBREC)
    
    - db__message_update_outgoing(): same as message__out_update but for
      server side (used on PUBREC to transition to wait_for_pubcomp)
    
    - db__message_delete_outgoing(): find and remove message from inflight
      queue on PUBACK/PUBCOMP, then call message__release_to_inflight to
      promote queued messages
    
    - db__message_remove_from_inflight(): call tr2q_unload_msg() to remove
      message from queue and clear pending flag on disk
    
    All functions use the tr2_queue API (tr2q_get_by_mid, tr2q_msg_json,
    tr2q_set_hard_flag, tr2q_unload_msg) and user_flag helpers instead of
    the old mosquitto DL_FOREACH linked-list approach.
    
